Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.09,0:00:03.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频由CuriosityStream赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.09,0:00:03.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,This episode of Primal Space is supported by CuriosityStream.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.85,0:00:10.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,前往下方链接免费观看上千部纪录片
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.85,0:00:10.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Watch thousands of documentaries for free by visiting curiositystream.com/primalspace.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.95,0:00:18.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,3月2日 太空叉首次发射了载人龙飞船前往国际空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.95,0:00:18.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the 2nd of March, SpaceX launched the Dragon 2 capsule on its first trip to the International Space Station
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.57,0:00:25.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,这次飞行的目的是在它真正载人前演示其可以安全运转
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.57,0:00:25.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was a test flight to show that the capsule could safely perform its job before it launches with humans onboard.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.14,0:00:32.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而在真正载人之前 载人龙飞船还要进行飞行中中止测试
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.14,0:00:32.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,However before that flight takes place, the Dragon 2 capsule will need to perform an in-flight abort test,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.50,0:00:34.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,效果会很爆炸
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.50,0:00:34.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,which could be very explosive.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.17,0:00:38.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频 我们将了解中止系统是如何在发射失败时保护宇航员的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.17,0:00:38.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this video, we're going to look at how the abort system is used
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.47,0:00:41.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频 我们将了解中止系统是如何在发射失败时保护宇航员的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.47,0:00:41.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,to protect the astronauts in the event of a failure.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.87,0:00:46.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们还将了解现实中中止系统工作的案例
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.87,0:00:46.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're also going to look at real life examples of the abort system in action
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.35,0:00:51.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,以及未来太空叉的中止测试将有多酷炫
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.35,0:00:51.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,and how the upcoming SpaceX abort test might provide quite a spectacle!
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.27,0:00:59.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,在1983年 俄罗斯(苏联)打算用联盟号送两名宇航员上太空
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.27,0:00:59.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Back in 1983, a Russian Soyuz rocket was scheduled to launch with 2 Cosmonauts onboard.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.32,0:01:03.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,起飞前90秒 一场大火突然吞噬了整个火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.32,0:01:03.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,90 Seconds before liftoff, an enormous fire engulfed the rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.25,0:01:10.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,控制小组立即触发发射逃逸系统 系统点火并把宇航员带到了安全地区
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.25,0:01:10.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,The control team triggered the launch escape system which quickly fired up and lifted the Cosmonauts to safety,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.42,0:01:13.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,几秒后 火箭爆炸了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.42,0:01:13.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,just seconds before the rocket exploded.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.97,0:01:17.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,着陆后 宇航员身体并无大碍 只是吓得不轻
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.97,0:01:17.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Upon landing, the Cosmonauts were in good health but slightly shaken,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.02,0:01:21.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,于是赶紧给他们撮口伏特加 点了根烟冷静冷静
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.02,0:01:21.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they were given vodka and cigarettes to help them relax.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.67,0:01:29.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉已经进行过发射台中止测试 可以在类似的情况中让宇航员幸免于难
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.67,0:01:29.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX have already performed a pad abort test, which would save the astronauts in a very similar scenario.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.82,0:01:33.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,但不是所有火箭都有发射逃逸系统
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.82,0:01:33.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, not all rockets have launch escape systems.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.40,0:01:39.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的独特设计让它难以拥有传统的发射逃逸系统
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.40,0:01:39.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Due to the unique design of the Space Shuttle, it wasn't practical to have a traditional launch escape system.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.45,0:01:44.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的首飞 哥伦比亚号 为两名飞行员装有弹射座椅
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.45,0:01:44.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,The initial flight of Space Shuttle Columbia included two ejector seats for the pilots,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.80,0:01:49.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这在航天飞机搭载超过两名航天员后就被拆掉了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.80,0:01:49.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,however these were removed once the Shuttle started flying more than 2 astronauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.56,0:01:53.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,取而代之的是宇航员可以在故障下操作的更多样的中止模式
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.56,0:01:53.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead, the Space Shuttle had a wide range of abort modes
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.57,0:01:56.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,取而代之的是宇航员可以在故障下操作的更多样的中止模式
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.57,0:01:56.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,which the astronauts would carry out in the event of a failure.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.60,0:02:00.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,其中包括飞行中打开逃生舱门 七人逃生后使用降落伞着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.60,0:02:00.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,One of these included opening the escape hatch mid-flight
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.87,0:02:05.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,其中包括飞行中打开逃生舱门 七人逃生后使用降落伞着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.87,0:02:05.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,with all seven astronauts bailing out and using parachutes to land.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.34,0:02:09.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这些中止模式都不能在像挑战者号那样突发故障让宇航员逃生
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.34,0:02:09.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, these abort modes would not be able to save the crew
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.20,0:02:13.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这些中止模式都不能在像挑战者号那样突发故障让宇航员逃生
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.20,0:02:13.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the event of a sudden failure similar to the Challenger disaster.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.97,0:02:20.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,发射逃逸系统的想法最初见于NASA在60年代早期的水星计划中
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.97,0:02:20.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,The idea for a launch escape system dates back to NASA's Mercury missions during the early 60's.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.85,0:02:23.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,当Atlas火箭发生故障时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.85,0:02:23.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the event of the Atlas rocket failing,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.50,0:02:29.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,水星号会立即点燃固体火箭 将返回舱拽离火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.50,0:02:29.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,the Mercury capsule would instantly fire up solid rocket motors to pull the capsule away from the rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.02,0:02:33.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后阿波罗任务中的逃逸系统与之非常相似
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.02,0:02:33.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,A very similar system was used during the Apollo missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:34.10,0:02:36.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了测试阿波罗的发射逃逸系统
Dialogue: 2,0:02:34.10,0:02:36.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to test the Apollo launch escape system,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.10,0:02:42.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,一个指令舱的模型被安装在名为"Little Joe 2号"的助推火箭上
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.10,0:02:42.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,a mockup of the command module was placed on top of a booster named Little Joe II.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.06,0:02:47.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,原计划是发射火箭 在一万英尺触发逃逸
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.06,0:02:47.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,The plan was to launch the rocket and trigger an abort once it reached 10,000 feet.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.28,0:02:53.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,但因为陀螺仪设置错误 火箭开始滚转
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.28,0:02:53.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, due to a mistake when setting up the gyros, the booster started to roll
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.07,0:02:56.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,并马上陷入失控状态并解体
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.07,0:02:56.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,and quickly became uncontrollable, causing it to break apart.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.05,0:03:02.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,这立即触发了中止 发射逃逸系统很快将指令舱拽离至安全地带
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.05,0:03:02.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,This instantly triggered an abort and the launch escape system quickly pulled the command module to safety.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.12,0:03:08.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,这次无心插柳的失败却成就了一次最真实的发射逃逸系统测试
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.12,0:03:08.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,This unexpected failure provided the most realistic test for the launch escape system.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.97,0:03:11.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是一次“相当成功的失败”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.97,0:03:11.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was a perfectly successful failure.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.67,0:03:17.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,载人龙飞船之后的中止测试也会是类似的流程
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.67,0:03:17.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,The upcoming abort test for the Dragon 2 capsule will follow a very similar plan.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.42,0:03:22.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号会先假装飞向国际空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.42,0:03:22.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Falcon 9 will launch as if it was heading towards the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.15,0:03:30.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,当到达最大动压时 九台梅林发动机关机 模拟推力骤减的故障
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.15,0:03:30.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once it reaches Max Q, the 9 Merlin engines on the Falcon 9 will shutdown to simulate a loss of thrust.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.07,0:03:35.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,载人龙飞船会检测到该故障并与猎鹰九号火箭分离
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.07,0:03:35.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Dragon capsule will detect this and separate from the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.07,0:03:40.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后立即点燃SuperDraco发动机 把飞船拽离火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.07,0:03:40.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,before quickly firing up its SuperDraco thrusters to pull it away from the booster.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.95,0:03:47.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,龙飞船之后会展开一系列的降落伞 然后溅落大西洋
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.95,0:03:47.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Dragon capsule will then deploy a series of parachutes before splashing down in the Atlantic Ocean.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,当触发中止后 猎鹰九号会变成完全不稳定状态
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the abort is triggered, the Falcon 9 will become completely unstable,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.97,0:03:57.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,导致其在差不多两倍音速的时候解体
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.97,0:03:57.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,causing it to break apart whilst travelling at twice the speed of sound.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.87,0:04:07.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,此时 猎鹰九号还载有32万磅(145吨)煤油和70万磅(317吨)液氧
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.87,0:04:07.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point, the Falcon 9 will be carrying 320,000 pounds of RP-1 fuel and 700,000 pounds of liquid oxygen.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:08.30,0:04:13.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,如此多的氧化剂会让燃料瞬间爆炸
Dialogue: 2,0:04:08.30,0:04:13.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,This oxidizer rich environment will cause most of that fuel to combust instantly,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.77,0:04:17.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,噼里啪啦炸成天空中一朵绚丽的烟花
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.77,0:04:17.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,creating an enormous fireball in the sky.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.62,0:04:21.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以当我们耐心等待太空叉首次载人上太空之前
Dialogue: 2,0:04:17.62,0:04:21.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,So as we patiently wait for SpaceX to launch their first humans into space,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.80,0:04:27.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,不如期待一下这次中止测试 肯定非常好看
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.80,0:04:27.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can look forward to this abort test, which promises to be quite a spectacle.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.52,0:04:32.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,同样好看的还有CuriosityStream的多种多样的纪录片
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.52,0:04:32.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another impressive spectacle is the range of documentaries on CuriosityStream.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.77,0:04:36.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,CuriosityStream是一个拥有海量纪录片资源的视频网站
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.77,0:04:36.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,CuriosityStream is a streaming service with tonnes of interesting documentaries,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.95,0:04:41.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,内容涵盖科学 自然 历史 科技
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.95,0:04:41.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,covering topics like: science, nature, history and technology.
